snippet: An influx of immigrants from Uzbekistan, which has a long history of success in fight sports, has transformed New York’s high school wrestling competition.
abstract: Young immigrants from Uzbekistan are becoming what may be the defining force in Brooklyn's high school wrestling world; at least nine high schools in Brooklyn and one in Queens have Uzbek immigrants on their teams, and those with the most have been among top teams in their divisions.
lead_paragraph: An influx of immigrants from Uzbekistan, which has a long history of success in fight sports, has transformed New York’s high school wrestling competition.

headline.main: In New York, Uzbek Immigrants Invigorate High School Wrestling
